Issue

 

Issues can be submitted by selecting Report Issue in the main menu.

In the new window fill following information:

  • Issue type. Select from the dropdown if you are submitting an Question, Bug, Improvement etc.
  • Name - short title of the issue
  • Description of the issue
  • Priority. Select from the dropdown if the priority is Minor, Medium, Major
  • Reporter. Change the reporter of the issue if needed.

Press Create button

 

The issue opens in edit mode. You can add any additional information like:

  • references to other items in the system
  • depends on  issues
  • attachments
  • detailed description of the issue. You can add screenshots and any details here.

Add additional information in the issue if needed and click Save.

You will receive mail notifications if the issue status changes.

 

You can check the progress on the issues that you are reporter of or watcher in the Issues tab on your personal profile

 

 

Provide additional information on an issue

If additional information is needed on an issue you will receive an e-mail notification to provide some clarifications on the issue.

To open the issue click on View Object button 

Once you open the issue you will notice that the status of the issue is "For clarification".

Check also the Comment section for any additional instructions on what information should be provided.

Open the issue by pressing the Edit button and add all information that you can provide in addition and/or replay in the comment section.

Once ready save the issue and press Clarified button. An e-mail notification will be send to the support. Your issue will become in Clarified status

You can also find all your issues that need more information under your dashboard - Issue tab,
